{"lemma":"فِيلِ","slug":"فِيلِ","root":"ف.#.ل","root_slug":"ف-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فِيل","root":"فيل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34996","n34997"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"elephant","examples":[{"text":"أَلَمْ تَرَ كَيْفَ فَعَلَ رَبُّكَ بِأَصْحَابِ ٱلْفِيلِ","english":"Have thou seen not how thy Lord dealt with the companions of the elephant?"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bishop (use the dual to pluralize)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nAkkadian 𒄠𒋛 (pīru)der.\nMiddle Persian pyl (/⁠pīl⁠/)bor.\nArabic فيل\nBorrowed from Middle Persian pyl (/⁠pīl⁠/), from Akkadian 𒄠𒋛 (pīru).\nCognate with Aramaic פִּילָא (pīlā) and Hebrew פיל (píl). Compare also Old Armenian փիղ (pʻił), Persian پیل (pil), Sanskrit पीलु (pīlu)."},"ipa":["/fiːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34996","headword_ar":"فَيْلٌ","root":"fyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n34997","headword_ar":"فِيلُ","root":"fyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elephant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Pyl","text_ar":"پيل"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoyaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuyuwlN","text_ar":"فُيُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyalapN","text_ar":"فِيَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, O, Msb, K;) not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoyilapN","text_ar":"اَفْيِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, S, O, Msb:) accord. to Sb."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiylN","text_ar":"فِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be originally of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolN","text_ar":"فُعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O,) pronounced with kesr because of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byDN","text_ar":"بيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but Akh says, this is not the case in the sing, but only in the pl.: (S, O:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K) ―         -b2-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN mivolu lawoni Alfiyli","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ مِثْلُ لَوْنِ الفِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A night like the colour of the elephant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a night that is black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and dust-coloured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one knows not the right course to pursue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the colours of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fyl","text_ar":"فيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being of this kind. (M, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA='u Alfiyli","text_ar":"دَا=ءُ الفِيلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The disease called by us the tumid Barbadoes leg;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the leg of the patient resembles that of the elephant by reason of its enormously-swollen state: not (as some have supposed it to be) elephantiasis; this latter being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ju*aAm","text_ar":"جُذَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.) [―         -b4-  And hence, likewise, used as an epithet,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiylN","text_ar":"فِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Heavy"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dull"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low, ignoble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b5-  And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN fiylu Alr~aA^oYi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ فِيلُ الرَّاْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man weak in respect of judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyoluhu","text_ar":"فِيْلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAy^iluhu","text_ar":"فَايِلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, M, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fay~iluhu","text_ar":"فَيِّلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, T, S, M, O, K,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEil","text_ar":"فَيْعِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAluhu","text_ar":"فَالُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAlN","text_ar":"فَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone. (S, K.) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak in respect of judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"erring in insight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl. of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoyaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, O, K:) but AO says, the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAy^il","text_ar":"فَايِل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who, inspecting, forms an opinion and errs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"if he err after examining a horse in all its states or conditions and forming an opinion respecting it from his inspection, [not while doing so,] he is not reckoned to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAy^l","text_ar":"فايل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","ISk","S","O","Msb","M","K","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}